The paper discusses the challenges of video streaming over wireless networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses video quality adaptation, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM) and information theory (cs.IT). The use of control theory for wireless transmission scheduling is a topic in systems and control (cs.SY) and the use of proportional-integral-derivative (PID) controllers is a topic in control theory (cs.MA).
